                <h2>Technical/R&D program management</h2>
                <p>WIDL can work with manufacturers (one-on-one, or in groups) on: existing programs, for cost-savings; tools/molds/dies
                    or parts being quoted, towards optimization; and specific projects to make, for cost-effectiveness. WIDL
                    can also structure R&D activities for production shops, from early concepts, literature and patent searches,
                    design and simulation, to prototyping and testing, with the transfer of knowledge benefiting contracting
                    shops and their patrons. WIDL can be part of any program and production team, or take on entire management
                    and R&D of applications for OEMs.</p>
            </div>
